ty of Karachi and its surrounding areas.</p></blockquote><script async src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"></script>'),(192,114,'_oembed_time_c03f5cbf429491192a0311448e3b3845','1553443980'),(194,102,'_oembed_0959d4e5a23f314e47ba8883368268a7','<blockquote class=\"embedly-card\" data-card-controls=\"1\" data-card-align=\"center\" data-card-theme=\"light\"><h4><a href=\"http://www.worldsrichestcountries.com/top_pakistan_exports.html\">Top Pakistan Exports</a></h4><p>Top Pakistan exports 2017</p></blockquote><script async src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"></script>'),(195,102,'_oembed_time_0959d4e5a23f314e47ba8883368268a7','1553444041'),(197,66,'_oembed_time_385f613483200aab475849399e1ebf29','1553447784'),(198,117,'_edit_lock','1553536071:1'),(200,117,'_oembed_385f613483200aab475849399e1ebf29','<blockquote class=\"embedly-card\" data-card-controls=\"1\" data-card-align=\"center\" data-card-theme=\"light\"><h4><a href=\"https://www.dawn.com/news/1377203\">How stocks will react to a weaker rupee</a></h4><p>AFTER having been shackled for a long time, the rupee has finally been left to find its true value against the US dollar in the market. Economists and analysts have expressed their dismay over the artificial propping up of the rupee. But former finance minister Ishaq Dar feared inflation would kick in if the rupee was allowed to depreciate.</p></blockquote><script async src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"></script>'),(201,117,'_oembed_time_385f613483200aab475849399e1ebf29','1553455055'),(206,121,'_edit_lock','1553449362:1'),(203,117,'_oembed_b3fb330a4f33a5669238c49734318034','<blockquote class=\"embedly-card\" data-card-controls=\"1\" data-card-align=\"center\" data-card-theme=\"light\"><h4><a href=\"https://www.thebalance.com/how-bonds-affect-the-stock-market-3305603\">Bonds Versus Stocks? Which Is Better for You?</a></h4><p>Bonds affect the stock market because they both compete for investors\' dollars. Bonds are safer than stocks, but they offer a lower return. As a result, when stocks go up in value, bonds go down. Stocks do well when the economy is booming. Consumers are buying and companies receive higher earnings thanks to higher demand.</p></blockquote><script async src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"></script>'),(204,117,'_oembed_time_b3fb330a4f33a5669238c49734318034','1553455056'),(211,117,'_oembed_cff921d467cf8d857f55375d9860ca98','<blockquote class=\"embedly-card\" data-card-controls=\"1\" data-card-align=\"center\" data-card-theme=\"light\"><h4><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SDdRRQugpU8\">Wall Street correction-role of bond yields and inflation</a></h4><p>John Authers reports from New York at the end of the wildest week on markets in two years, as worries about inflation suddenly prompted a rethink about share prices.</p></blockquote><script async src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"></script>'),(208,121,'_oembed_bdf5e1d715518b8e6430f50032f51a74','<blockquote class=\"embedly-card\" data-card-controls=\"1\" data-card-align=\"center\" data-card-theme=\"light\"><h4><a href=\"https://www.thebalance.com/what-are-treasury-bills-notes-and-bonds-3305609\">How Treasury Bills, Notes and Bonds Work</a></h4><p>The difference between bills, notes, and bonds are the lengths until maturity: Treasury bills are issued for terms less than a year. Treasury notes are issued for terms of two, three, five, and 10 years. Treasury bonds are issued for terms of 30 years. They were reintroduced in February 2006.</p></blockquote><script async src=\"//cdn.embedly.com/widgets/platform.js\" charset=\"UTF-8\"></script>'),(209,121,'_oembed_time_bdf5e1d715518b8e6430f50032f51a74','1553449504'),(212,117,'_oembed_time_cff921d467cf8d857f55375d9860ca98','1553455058'),(214,74,'_oembed_6c9fe60bfbb299e271637aa426a4b260','<blockquote class=\"embedly-card\" data-card-controls=\"1\" data-card-align=\"center\" da