ich\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-youtube\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=judrJnp8OWk\n</div><figcaption> <br>Kevin O\'Leary - Real Estate Investment Advice </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->','Kevin O\'Leary Videos','','inherit','closed','closed','','61-revision-v1','','','2019-03-23 18:59:30','2019-03-23 18:59:30','',61,'http://localhost/my_library/2019/03/23/61-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(66,1,'2019-03-23 20:22:48','2019-03-23 20:22:48','<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Invest not more than 5% in a company.</li><li>Invest not more than 20% in a sector.</li><li>Invest in Free Cash Flow generating Dividend paying stocks.</li><li>Identify sector which are depended on rupee depreciation, interest &amp; inflation rate sensitive. And invest in them because correction happen once every 4 to 6 years after a growth period.</li><li>50% Corporate Bond &amp; 50% Stocks</li><li>There is nothing nobler than working for yourself to gain financial freedom, to do what you want.</li><li>Pros of technology is that it increases productivity, but the con is that it creates distraction.</li><li></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>FOUR THEMES TO PLAY</strong></li><li><strong>3D (Defensive, devaluation friendly, high D/Y): </strong>E&amp;Ps, IPPs, Fertz, Textile fit the bill .</li><li> <strong>Policy rate hike:</strong> Rate hike plays, NPLs are under control, stock prices should bring banks in favor.</li><li><strong>Exports focus:</strong> Rebate, reduction in production cost &amp; freight incentives likely. Key beneficiaries could be cement, value added textile, auto parts, leather.</li><li><strong>IMF Reforms: </strong>Energy remain major area for fiscal consolidation. Besides power tariff hike, controlover T&amp;D losses and circular debt bode well We prefer IPPs.<