 for yourself to gain financial freedom, to do what you want.</li><li>Pros of technology is that it increases productivity, but the con is that it creates distraction.</li><li></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><li><strong>FOUR THEMES TO PLAY</strong></li><li><strong>3D (Defensive, devaluation friendly, high D/Y): </strong>E&amp;Ps, IPPs, Fertz, Textile fit the bill .</li><li> <strong>Policy rate hike:</strong> Rate hike plays, NPLs are under control, stock prices should bring banks in favor.</li><li><strong>Exports focus:</strong> Rebate, reduction in production cost &amp; freight incentives likely. Key beneficiaries could be cement, value added textile, auto parts, leather.</li><li><strong>IMF Reforms: </strong>Energy remain major area for fiscal consolidation. Besides power tariff hike, controlover T&amp;D losses and circular debt bode well We prefer IPPs.</li><li><strong>Our top ten picks are:</strong> PPL, MARI, EFERT, FATIMA, MCB, UBL, LUCK, NML, EPCL, HUBC</li><li><strong>Which sectors are we negative?</strong> Refineries, leveraged cement players, gas utilities, textile spinning, autos, consumer appliances (WAVES is an exception), flat rolled steel, pharma</li></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://www.dawn.com/news/1377203\",\"type\":\"rich\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"dawn-com\",\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-dawn-com\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.dawn.com/news/1377203\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->','My Investing Principles','','inherit','closed','closed','','66-autosave-v1','','','2019-03-24 17:16:22','2019-03-24 17:16:22','',66,'http://localhost/my_library/2019/03/24/66-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(118,1,'2019-03-24 17:17:17','2019-03-24 17:17:17','<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Invest not more than 5% in a company.</li><li>Invest not more than 20% in a sector.</li><li>Invest in Free Cash Flow generating Dividend payi