 the growth &amp; expansion of the business. Business can use this cash to expand their business.<br>3. It shows that promoters &amp; owners doesn\'t have confidence in the growth of their own business.<br>4. They don\'t know how and where to expand and grow their business. Read company annual reports to know if they have plans for future growth or not. (Sector also)<br>5. A good business remains cash rich to expand and grow their business (they follow growth philosophy). And never pays high dividend to the shareholders. (Cash Rich Companies like Reliance etc)<br>Every company has investment/ capex cycle. Companies stocks reaps benefits when capex cycle is over.<br><strong>BONUS TIPS:</strong><br>1. Analyze overall evaluation if company\'s return is 30% and dividend yield is 2% than net return is 32%. And if another company\'s return is -20% and dividend yield is 10% than your net return is -10%.<br>2. Select companies with good net return and hold them for 1 year than through systematic withdrawal withdraw amount according to your need like 10% yearly. In india dividend is tax-free and stocks after 1 year is tax-free.</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C0Z3YDwGKUk\",\"type\":\"rich\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-youtube\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C0Z3YDwGKUk\n</div><figcaption> Investment Options - To Generate Double Digit Returns | HINDI </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:core-embed/youtube -->\n\n<!-- wp:core-embed/youtube {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KCGztq2mxDI\",\"type\":\"rich\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed-youtube wp-block-embed is-type-rich is-provider-youtube\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KCGztq2m